==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stage director
<hw>Stage director</hw>. <fld>(Theat.)</fld> <def>One who prepares a
play for production. He arranges the details of the stage settings, the
business to be used, all stage effects, and instructs the actors,
excepting usually the star, in the general interpretation of their
parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stage fright</ent>⟦br⟧
